{"word":"G5168 - τρυμαλιά - trymaliá - troo-mal-ee-ah' - Eye","slug":"G5168","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">τρυμαλιά</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>trymaliá"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>troo-mal-ee-ah'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Eye"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C4;&#x03C1;&#x03C5;&#x03BC;&#x03B1;&#x03BB;&#x03B9;&#x03B1;&#x0301; - trumalia</b> - <i>troo-mal-ee-ah'</i><p/>From a derivative of <b>&#x03C4;&#x03C1;&#x03C5;&#x0301;&#x03C9;&#x0301;</b> <b>truo&#x0304;</b> (to <i>wear</i> away; akin to the base of <a href=\"#/G5134\">G5134</a>, <a href=\"#/G5147\">G5147</a> and <a href=\"#/G5176\">G5176</a>); an <i>orifice</i>, that is, a needle&rsquo;s <i>eye</i>: - eye. Compare <a href=\"#/G5169\">G5169</a>."}]}